divs: Sighting DetailsUnlike what the previous person posting about the "star" object disappearing before it crossed the moon, what i saw was the moon was behind the house while i was in the front of the house & i looked up & saw this star like thing going right across the sky, away from the moon & i was thinking to myself it's too fast to be an airplane & it's not blinking & it's way too white bright to be any kind of airplane light, it went by kinda fast & then just went dimmer & dimmer way too fast. It went towards Trenton. I'm outside quite frequently, being a smoker who smokes outside, i have become very familiar with the night sky. I have seen alot of unexplainable occurrences. This just adds to my list of many.
Summary: Saw what looked like a star going horizantal then just disappearing
